Two siblings, Janelle and Terrence, are visiting their friends Amy and Sarah. Terrence has just won a game of checkers against Amy for the second time in a row.
&ldquo;Hey Sarah,&rdquo; Amy said. &ldquo;This checkerboard reminds me of the magic trick you showed me yesterday.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Magic trick?&rdquo; asked Janelle.
&ldquo;The one where you cut up the grid,&rdquo; Amy prompted her big sister. &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s show Terrence and Janelle!&rdquo;
&ldquo;Okay,&rdquo; said Sarah, grinning.

The five crew members of a small pirate ship have just completed a raid in another crew&rsquo;s territory, and they now have 100 gold coins to split among themselves.
&ldquo;What a raid!&rdquo; says the captain Anastasia. &ldquo;Look at the feather in my hat &ndash; it&rsquo;s been torn to shreds.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Aye,&rdquo; agrees the first mate Bartholomew. &ldquo;I have a new hole in my coat.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Lucky my compass didn&rsquo;t get smashed while we were retreating back to sea,&rdquo; remarks the navigator Cornelius.
